        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35340",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=klassicd",
                        "name": "klassicd",
                        "displayName": "michael depetrillo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "__toString() method fixed.  According to Gdata docs you have to choose between absolute time, days, minutes or hours so I left the switch statement.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=klassicd",
                        "name": "klassicd",
                        "displayName": "michael depetrillo",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-16T22:45:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-16T22:45:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35448",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks for the fix, Michael. Looks good.\r\n\r\nI'm reopening this, because this point still needs to be addressed:\r\n\r\nbq. 4. Not 100% sure on this one - but as far as I understand this class and associated GData API, it can have either an absolute time, or a set of Days, Hours, Minutes and Seconds set. Therefor, it should not use elseif-statements, since a reminder can be in 3 hours AND 12 minutes.\r\n\r\nThat should be simple, I'll go ahead and fix that.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-21T15:10:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-21T15:10:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35449",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I looked into the GData API and found that Michael is right. The GData API only handles values consisting of one type, and suggests converting them to the smallest type required - so 2 days, 17 hours should be converted into (2x24 + 17) hours.\r\n\r\nHowever, when displaying (which I presume what the __toString() is intended for?), it would definitely be nicer to have the conversion into separate units so fixing it does seem to be the way to go.\r\n\r\nAs a suggestion, when you're working on it: you might want to refactor this functionality into a separate public method, returning an array of units. Then use that to build up the string.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-21T15:36:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-21T15:36:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35450",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Further info:\r\n\r\nThe limitation mentioned above is actually part of their description of the PHP API:  http:\/\/code.google.com\/intl\/en-UK\/apis\/calendar\/data\/2.0\/developers_guide_php.html#Reminders - this creates a bit of a chicken\/egg problem. Fix the behaviour to be more flexible or stay compatible with the official docs?\r\n\r\nInternally, the Gdata protocol always uses minutes, based on http:\/\/code.google.com\/intl\/en-UK\/apis\/calendar\/data\/2.0\/developers_guide_protocol.html#Reminders",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tubularbell",
                        "name": "tubularbell",
                        "displayName": "Sander Bol",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-21T15:53:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-21T15:53:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
